                <p>Ratan Tata, a name synonymous with the Tata Group, has left an indelible mark on the conglomerate’s journey toward becoming a global powerhouse. Taking over the reins in 1991 as chairman, Tata's tenure saw the company undergo a massive transformation, expanding beyond traditional sectors into new industries, markets, and technologies. Under his leadership, Tata Group diversified into automotive, telecommunications, IT services, and global steel production.</p>
                <p>One of the most defining moments of his leadership was the acquisition of global brands like Jaguar Land Rover in 2008 and the takeover of Corus Steel in 2007. These bold moves not only elevated the brand's international stature but also cemented Tata Group’s presence in key markets like Europe and North America. His ability to foresee global trends and take calculated risks contributed immensely to the company's expansion.</p>
                <div class="row  m-b20">
