                </div>
                <p>Beyond business, Ratan Tata is revered for his strong commitment to ethical business practices and corporate responsibility. He championed the group's investment in social welfare, education, and healthcare initiatives through the Tata Trusts, ensuring that Tata Group continues to have a positive impact on society.</p>
                <p>Even after stepping down as chairman in 2012, Ratan Tata's influence remains significant. He continues to mentor future leaders and provide strategic insights, making sure that Tata Group remains true to its values of integrity, innovation, and excellence. His leadership period, often seen as a golden era for the company, laid a solid foundation for future growth and diversification.</p>
                <p>In conclusion, Ratan Tata's contributions have not only shaped Tata Group into a global conglomerate but also instilled a legacy of leadership and responsibility that continues to guide the company today.</p>
            </div>

        </div>
